Christina Baker Bio:
Nurse for thirty years including inpatient pediatric surgery at UCSF and UNC Chapel Hill, pediatric outpatient ambulatory clinic, school health consultant at Denver Public Schools and Childrens Hospital Colorado, nurse informaticist at Children’s Hospital Colorado. Currently Assistant Professor in the CU College of Nursing. PhD in Health Systems from CU May 2023, Master’s in Healthcare Informatics from CU May 2014 and BSN from University of San Francisco December 1989. I am in the CSPH Health Data Science certificate program and will finish this spring—interest in research to improve health information exchange ( HIE) between hospitals and public health systems. Husband and I love to travel.
